"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144392","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>Initial Industry Advice is provided on a “private and confidential” basis. I therefore do not intend to publish the Initial Industry Advice.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2019-09-09T13:27:51.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144392/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144392/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish the Initial Industry Advice received from the Rail Delivery Group in January 2017 as part of the Government’s planning process for the development of control period 6 from (a) 2019 to (b) 2024.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144393","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>Since the Review started in September 2018, Keith Williams has held regular meetings with the Department. Mr Williams has made clear that his Review must not stop or delay investment and innovation.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2019-09-09T13:08:19.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144393/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144393/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","West Coast Partnership Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions took place between his Department and Government's Rail Review chair Keith Williams prior to his Department's decision to award the West Coast Partnership franchise to a consortium of First Group and Trenitalia on 14 August 2019.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286259"
