"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144435","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no plans to deploy any additional military personnel to Northern Ireland, nor have we received any requests from other Government Departments or civil authorities to support policing on the Irish border.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-09-09T09:59:33.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144435/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144435/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144435/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-03","Borders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to support policing on the Irish border in the event that the UK leaves the EU without an agreement.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","286196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144436","Home Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>Much of our national security cooperation with our European partners takes place outside EU structures and so is not dependent on our membership. We continue to work intensively with operational partners to ensure that we are ready for any eventuality.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2019-09-09T15:01:58.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144436/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144436/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144436/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-09-03","Databases: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of the implications for national security of the end of data sharing with EU member states.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","286197"
