"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142806","Scotland Office","false","2019-09-06","<p>The Facebook ad library contains data on every active ad. When the Department has active ads they automatically appear in the ad library under ‘UK Government Scotland’.</p><p> </p><p>The Facebook ad library also contains data on some inactive ads on topics determined by Facebook. To date this includes two ads shown by the Department, both of which pertained to Brexit.</p>","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack",,"2019-09-06T10:58:12.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142806/answer","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142806/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142806/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-09-02","Scotland Office: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, for what reasons social media adverts produced by his Department do not appear in the Facebook ad library.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","284193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142807","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","HMRC recognise that some of their customers may need extra support. HMRC’s contact centre advisors are trained to identify customers who may need extra help above and beyond the help that can be provided by phone. Customers are passed to specialist teams and where appropriate, HMRC will meet customers face-to-face in their own home or somewhere convenient to them. Further information can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/dealing-hmrc-additional-needs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/dealing-hmrc-additional-needs</a>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-09-09T13:13:20.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142807/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142807/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142807/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-02","Taxation: Self-assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what support HMRC provides to assist people with dyslexia complete tax return forms.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","284196"
