"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142838","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2019-10-01","<p>The Department does not hold this data as it is not recorded at such a level.</p><p> </p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2019-10-01T13:59:49.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142838/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142838/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142838/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2019-09-02","Department for Exiting the European Union: Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how much his Department spent on refreshments in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142839","Department for International Trade","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department for International Trade has spent a total of £276,815 on refreshments in the financial years 2017/18 and 2018/19. This cost includes both the UK and overseas.</p><p> </p><p>The breakdown is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Amount</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2017 – March 2018</p></td><td><p>£118,579</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2018 – March 2019</p></td><td><p>£158,236</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£276,815</strong> <strong> </strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Staff at the Department for International Trade are located across more than one hundred countries and as we prepare to leave the EU, our ministers and Department for International Trade staff regularly travel overseas to build relationships with key global trading partners and the Department uses refreshment for diplomatic entertainment on trade issues.</p><p> </p><p>This includes through the 14 trade working groups we have set up across 21 countries to advance the UK's trade and investment relationships and scope out the potential for future free trade agreements. The figures include overseas spending.</p>","Bournemouth West","Conor Burns",,"2019-09-09T14:26:47.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142839/answer","Biography information for Conor Burns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142839/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142839/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-09-02","Department for International Trade: Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much her Department spent on refreshments in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142840","Leader of the House","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Office of the Leader of the House of Commons is part of the Cabinet Office and is supported by Cabinet Office staff. I refer the Hon. member to question 285090 and the answer to be provided by the Department. Spend on refreshments is paid in accordance with the Department’s procedures.</p>","North East Somerset","Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg",,"2019-09-09T16:39:44.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142840/answer","Biography information for Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142840/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142840/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2019-09-02","Leader of the House of Commons: Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how much his Department spent on refreshments in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284275"
