"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142842","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-09-06","<p>In answering this question the Department has taken refreshments to mean tea, coffee and biscuits. Data for 2017 is only available for the period of April to December due to a change in how the data was captured. For these months in 2017 there was a spend of £704.00 on refreshments. In 2018, the spend on refreshments was £3,464.38.</p>","Skipton and Ripon","Julian Smith",,"2019-09-06T11:25:47.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142842/answer","Biography information for Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142842/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142842/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-09-02","Northern Ireland Office: Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much his Department spent on refreshments in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142843","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department does not hold central records for expenditure on refreshments. However, the following restrictions apply to all staff with effect from August 2010:</p><p> </p><ul><li>No lunches, tea or coffees can be ordered for any internal meeting (i.e. a meeting between MoJ staff). Water is freely available in our offices.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>For all external meetings (i.e. a meeting between MoJ staff and external stakeholders), lunch, tea and coffee purchases require Director-level sign-off and are only allowed in exceptional circumstances.</li></ul><p> </p><p>To provide information on departmental expenditure on refreshments would involve disproportionate cost.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-09-09T12:52:25.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142843/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142843/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142843/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-09-02","Ministry of Justice: Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much his Department spent on refreshments in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284312"
