"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142866","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>During the financial year 2018/2019, the Department spent £108,896.61 on ministerial travel. This was broken down into £15,643.94 on first class (business class) travel, and £93,252.67 on second class (economy class).</p>","Skipton and Ripon","Julian Smith",,"2019-09-09T11:23:34.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142866/answer","Biography information for Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142866/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-09-02","Northern Ireland Office: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) first class, (b) second class and (c) in total in 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142867","Leader of the House","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Office of the Leader of the House of Commons is part of the Cabinet Office and is supported by Cabinet Office staff. I refer the Hon. member to question 284952 and the answer to be provided by the Department.</p><p> </p>","North East Somerset","Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","285126","2019-09-09T16:38:36.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142867/answer","Biography information for Mr Jacob Rees-Mogg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142867/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2019-09-02","Leader of the House of Commons: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how much his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) first class, (b) second class and (c) in total in 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284372"
