"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142882","Department for Education","false","2019-09-09","<p>We want parents to have access to a range of affordable childcare, giving them increased flexibility in their working hours and helping children thrive in the crucial early years. That is why the department is investing £3.5 billion in our early education offers this year alone. The cost of 30 hours free childcare is set in table 1, attached. The total for 2017-18 is due to rounding.</p><p>The number of children that have benefitted from 30 hours free childcare in each year is set out in table 2, attached.</p><p>In total, around 600,000 children aged 3 and 4 years old benefitted from a 30 hours place throughout the first 2 years of delivery.</p><p>We do not hold data on estimates of the number of parents that have benefitted from the 30 hours entitlement in England.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284299 ; 284395 ; 285420 ; 285422","2019-09-09T14:23:32.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142882/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142882/answer","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_30_hours_childcare.xls","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142882/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people used the 30 hours free childcare scheme in England in (a) 2017-18 and (b) 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","284402"
