"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142885","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","<p>Tax-Free Childcare (TFC) provides support to parents of 20% of their childcare costs, up to a cap of £2000 per child per year.</p><p> </p><p>The official statistics publication ‘Tax-Free Childcare Statistics’ (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tax-free-childcare-statistics-june-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tax-free-childcare-statistics-june-2019</a>) contains a monthly breakdown of Government costs.</p><p> </p><p>The Government does not collect data on the number of hours of childcare being subsidised by TFC. It is therefore not possible to calculate the cost to the Government of TFC per hour of childcare subsidised.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2019-09-09T09:38:44.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142885/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142885/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142885/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost is to the public purse of tax free childcare per hour.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","284410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142886","Department for Education","false","2019-09-09","<p>We want parents to have access to a range of affordable childcare, giving them increased flexibility in their working hours and helping children thrive in the crucial early years. That is why the department is investing £3.5 billion in our early education offers this year alone. The cost of 30 hours free childcare is set in table 1, attached. The total for 2017-18 is due to rounding.</p><p>The number of children that have benefitted from 30 hours free childcare in each year is set out in table 2, attached.</p><p>In total, around 600,000 children aged 3 and 4 years old benefitted from a 30 hours place throughout the first 2 years of delivery.</p><p>We do not hold data on estimates of the number of parents that have benefitted from the 30 hours entitlement in England.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284395 ; 284402 ; 285420 ; 285422","2019-09-09T14:23:32.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142886/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142886/answer","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_30_hours_childcare.xls","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142886/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many parents use the 30 hours free childcare scheme.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","284299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142887","Department for Education","false","2019-09-06","<p>​We want parents to have access to a range of affordable childcare, giving them increased flexibility in their working hours and helping children thrive in the crucial early years. That is why the Department for Education is investing £3.5 billion in our early education offers this year alone.</p><p>The 30 hours childcare entitlement provides an additional 570 hours of funded childcare to working parents of 3 and 4 year olds across the year. The 570 hours are in addition to the 570 hours already provided under the universal 15 hours free childcare entitlement. While many providers will offer 30 hours of funded childcare per week during term time (38 weeks of the year), all free entitlements can be ‘stretched’ by taking fewer hours per week over up to 52 weeks of the year to cover both term-time and the school holidays.</p><p>To ensure that parents can make informed decisions on their choice of childcare, the department’s statutory guidance for local authorities states that providers should publish a statement of how they deliver the free entitlements and any additional charges they impose for optional activities outside of the entitlement.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch",,"2019-09-06T16:52:01.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142887/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142887/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many weeks is the offering of 30 hours free childcare spread across the year.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","284412"
