"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142948","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-09-09","<p>As of 31 December 2018, there were 695 staff employed by the National Probation Service in the Wales probation region.</p><p> </p><p>Prison and Probation workforce statistics are published quarterly, more information can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/national-offender-management-service-workforce-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/national-offender-management-service-workforce-statistics</a>.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-09-09T11:28:19.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142948/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142948/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142948/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-09-02","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many staff were employed by probation services in Wales in 2018.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","284444"
