"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142954","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>The United Kingdom is committed to promoting and defending the human rights of all individuals. We have discussed issues affecting indigenous people with the Brazilian authorities and have regular contact with the Brazilian National Foundation for Indigenous People (FUNAI), which is responsible for protecting indigenous people in Brazil.</p>","Tamworth","Christopher Pincher",,"2019-09-09T11:43:02.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142954/answer","Biography information for Christopher Pincher","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142954/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142954/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Brazil: Indigenous Peoples","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Brazilian counterpart on the protection of indigenous tribes in the Amazon rainforest.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","284202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142955","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-05","<p>We believe that meaningful political dialogue, taken forward by Hong Kong under its high degree of autonomy, is the best way to resolve the current impasse. It is important that the basic freedoms enshrined in the Sino-British Joint Declaration are maintained.</p><p>The Sino-British Joint Declaration is a legally binding treaty, registered with the UN, that remains in force. The UK, as a co-signatory, has an obligation to monitor its implementation closely, and we are committed to doing so.</p><p>The Prime Minister discussed developments in Hong Kong with other leaders at the recent G7 Summit, and the Foreign Secretary has recently spoken with Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi and Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-09-05T14:17:56.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142955/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142955/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142955/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Hong Kong: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what diplomatic steps his Department is taking to ease tensions in Hong Kong.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","284203"
