"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143019","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>The UK was not a party to the agreement to establish de-escalation zones in Syria made by Russia, Turkey and Iran in 2017. We are gravely concerned by the ongoing military action by Russia and the Syrian regime in Idlib, including strikes which have hit civilian infrastructure. All parties should respect the de-escalation zone and agreed ceasefire, abide by their obligations under international humanitarian law and act to protect civilians.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-09-09T15:09:52.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143019/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143019/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143019/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-02","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans are in place to uphold the no-fly zone and de-escalation zone in the province of Idlib, Syria.","false","Biography information for Carol Monaghan","Glasgow North West","Carol Monaghan","284597"
